<subSubSection pageNumber="704" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="704">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="704">Note:</emphasis>
The varietal epithet was originally spelled 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“adrachnites”">&quot;adrachnites&quot;</normalizedToken>
in the protologue but was subsequently corrected by Linnaeus. Rothmaler (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="704">Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg.</emphasis>
49: 280. 1940) treated this as the basionym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) L. (1754)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1754" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1754" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Ophrys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arachnites">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="704">O. arachnites</emphasis>
(L.) L. (1754)
</taxonomicName>
, followed by Greuter (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="704">Candollea</emphasis>
44: 566. 1989). However, Britten (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="704">J. Bot.</emphasis>
47, Suppl. 1909; 50: 312-314. 1912) argued that 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="704">
&quot;
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1754" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Ophrys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arachnites">O. arachnites</taxonomicName>
&quot;
</emphasis>
resulted from a typographic error. Stearn (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="704">
Introd. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ray’s">Ray's</normalizedToken>
Syn. Meth. Stirp. Brit.
</emphasis>
(Ray Soc. ed.): 42-68. 1973) evidently agreed as he did not list the name as new.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
